---
title: React Native - Style
---
## React Native - Style

In a traditional webpage, you would need to define a CSS in order to change the style of a webpage. 
With React Native, you don't have to use a special language or syntax to define styles. You would just use Javascript. 

To do so, you would create a style prop. Here is a simple example: 

```js 
import React, { Component } from 'react';
import { AppRegistry, StyleSheet, Text, View } from 'react-native';

export default class CodeCamp extends Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <View>
        <Text style={styles.red}>just red</Text>
        <Text style={styles.bigblue}>just bigblue</Text>
        <Text style={[styles.bigblue, styles.red]}>bigblue, then red</Text>
        <Text style={[styles.red, styles.bigblue]}>red, then bigblue</Text>
      </View>
    );
  }
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  bigblue: {
    color: 'blue',
    fontWeight: 'bold',
    fontSize: 30,
  },
  red: {
    color: 'red',
  },
});

// skip this line if using Create React Native App
AppRegistry.registerComponent('FreeCodeCamp', () => CodeCamp);
```

